Linda Maserame Motlhalo of South Africa scores a penalty during the 2022 Women's Africa Cup of Nations semi-final match between South Africa and Zambia. BackpagePix/Samuel Shivambu CASABLANCA - Banyana Banyana are through to their sixth Women's Africa Cup of Nations final after seeing off a stubborn Zambian side in the semis. The Copper Queens surprised Banyana in the first half with a solid game plan as they denied their more fancied opponents space and time on the ball. However, in the send half both sides created a few goalscoring opportunities before South Africa were awarded a soft penalty. READ: Banyana Banyana book World Cup spot Jermaine Seoposenwe was fouled in the box and VAR intervened. Playmaker Linda Motlhalo coolly converted the resultant spot kick on a stroke of full-time. South Africa will now take on either the defending champions Nigeria or hosts Morocco in Saturday's final.